Hey! 
Sorry need some clarification on this:

NGA MARC metadata will only display when Fiche in selected in viewer?

Then what bibliographical records will display for digital surrogates?

Have no recollection of this being discussed in project call, an example would be helpful to understand.

Thanks!

(And hello to the ones i do not as of yet know!)

@lightgivener My understanding is that what we talked about is:
* When you first load the page, the microfiche should display with the NGA MARC metadata
* When you switch to a different digital object, it should display the metadata associated with that digital object (replacing the NGA MARC metadata)
* If there is no microfiche or other digital objects, then we can display the NGA MARC metadata as a fallback

Is that not how you remember it?

Hey! I thought the outside surrogate manifests would not even come with their MARC sets, but only the Manifest would be submitted. And then basic copy info would be accessable in the Viewer info section of the right?

Your version does make sense but no this is actually not what I remeber. I don't have much time now but lets check in on this again soonish!

thanks!

Hi @lightgivener, nice to meet you! I can't really add to the use case portion of this discussion.

But @cwulfman and I want to leave some implementation notes on next steps for ourselves for next week:
We've got a new `imported_metadata` field on the Version model. Next step is to populate it during the getty ingest scripts which were added in https://github.com/pulibrary/cicognara-rails/pull/354. In particular, we expect to add a test around https://github.com/pulibrary/cicognara-rails/pull/354/files#diff-8de88da2a1e2b66150c9d386ef5fc2daR31 that we're indexing a hash into `imported_metadata` with keys pulled from https://github.com/pulibrary/cicognara-rails/blob/3d648ffd5142bf246ab6f63d33b9c384a5943d42/app/controllers/catalog_controller.rb#L109-L131.

Tooling is set up to then present those hashes via solr documents in metadata divs on the show page.

Final step will be to hide / show those divs in response to click events on the tabs which currently control the viewer display.

We'll also need to explicitly test that the third case, where there are no versions but we want to still display the metadata, remains true.
